text.paragraph: Includes: History of Present Illness from this encounter

paragraph.content: Matthew Lewis is a 72 year old female.
preliminary background HPI [use for free text].
- Allergy list reviewed
- Problem list reviewed
- Medication list reviewed

Mrs Fontanez is a 72-year-old female with hypertension, dyslipidemia, chronic diastolic heart failure, chronic kidney disease a stage III A, history of left breast cancer status post surgery in 2009, chemo and radiation, venous insufficiency status post Left GSV ablation 1/2016, left SSV venaseal 10/2019, sickle cell trait, chronic pain syndrome,COPD and prediabetes who came in for transfer of care visit.
Last mammogram was about 3 years ago, as per patient with normal results. She has pmhx of right breast cancer.
Last Bone Density was also a long time ago, needs to be updated.
She has a total hysterectomy, no pap smear needed at this time.
She had a colonoscopy about about 5 years ago, as per patient with normal results and she does not want to updated it anymore.
The most recent lab work was done on January/9/2023: Hemoglobin 11.8, platelets 268, glucose 113, GFR 53.8, urinalysis negative,

She is also following up with ENT in regards dizziness for which she underwent VNG and she is a scheduled for an MRI of the internal auditory canal with gadolinium enhancement to evaluate to rule out acoustic neuroma. The patient is taking promethazine prn for vertigo because meclizine did n't work.

I reviewed 55 pages of the cardiology DR Sarah; she had LHC 12/2016 with mild CAD,LHC 6/2020-no evidence of obstructive coronary artery disease. Carotid ultrasound 1/2020 bilateral ICA 20-30% The patient is taking BB and nitro sl prn to treat the angina.

She is complaining of recurrent UTI and kidney issues that started yrs ago. She has taken OTC Azo with no improvement. She has followed up with Urology and has completed multiple procedures with some improvement but the issue has not completely resolved. The patient stated that she is having dysuria, urinary frequency, pelvic pain and bladder spasm since last Monday. The patient was unable to be seen by her prior PCP and she called again today and I decided to see her. She denies chills, fever, n/v, hematuria, hx kidney stones, diarrhea or flank pain.
